4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING STATEWIDE BALLOT ISSUE LAWS; REQUIRING A
5 POLL OF THE LEGISLATURE ON STATEWIDE INITIATIVES; REQUIRING THE RESULTS OF THE
6 LEGISLATIVE POLL OR LEGISLATIVE REFERRAL VOTE TO APPEAR ON THE BALLOT; AMENDING
7 SECTIONS 13-27-401 AND 13-27-501, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN
8 APPLICABILITY DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Legislative poll -- statewide initiatives. (1) Within 5 working days after
13 the 4-week cutoff deadline established in 13-27-301(1) for submitting signed sheets or sections of petitions with
14 original signatures, the secretary of state shall mail a ballot to each member of the legislature on each
15 statewide initiative received.
16 (2) The secretary of state shall send the ballot required in subsection (1) to all legislators by using
17 any reasonable and reliable means, including electronic delivery, that contains:
18 (a) a copy of the statewide initiative petition;
19 (b) a ballot that includes the following options:
20 (i) support the statewide initiative;
21 (ii) do not support the statewide initiative; or
22 (iii) do not have a position on the statewide initiative; and
23 (c) the date by which legislators shall return the ballot, which may not be more than 20 calendar
24 days after the date the ballots were sent.
25 (3) A legislator may cast and return a vote by delivering the ballot in person, by mailing the ballot,
26 or by sending the ballot by facsimile transmission or electronic mail to the office of the secretary of state. A
27 legislator may not change the legislator's vote after the ballot is received by the secretary of state.
28 (4) The secretary of state shall tally the votes within 1 working day after the date for the return of
