5 Section 2. Section 13-27-401, MCA, is amended to read:
6 "13-27-401. Voter information pamphlet. (1) The secretary of state shall prepare for printing a voter
7 information pamphlet containing information relevant to the election, including but not limited to the following
8 information for each statewide ballot issue to be voted on at an election, as applicable:
9 (a) ballot title, fiscal statement if applicable, and complete text of the issue;
10 (b) the form in which the issue will appear on the ballot;
11 (c) arguments advocating approval and rejection of the issue; and
12 (d) rebuttal arguments;
13 (e) for a statewide initiative, the summary results of the legislative poll provided for in [section 1],
14 listed by the majority vote within each political party as follows:
15 [Most or Every] [partisan affiliation] legislator(s) voted to [support, oppose, or to not take a position on]
16 [statewide initiative number and title]; and
17 (f) for a statewide referendum, the summary results of the legislative referral vote, listed by the
18 majority vote within each political party as follows:
19 [Most or Every] [partisan affiliation] legislator(s) voted to [support, oppose, or to not take a position on]
20 [statewide referendum number and title].
21 (2) The pamphlet must also contain a notice advising the recipient as to where additional copies of
22 the pamphlet may be obtained.
23 (3) Whenever more than one statewide ballot issue is to be voted on at a single election, the
24 secretary of state may publish a single pamphlet for all of the statewide ballot issues. The secretary of state
25 may arrange the information in the order that seems most appropriate, but the information for all statewide
26 ballot issues in the pamphlet must be presented in the same order.
27 (4) The secretary of state may prescribe by rule the format and manner of submission of the
28 arguments concerning the statewide ballot issue."
