2 Section 3. Section 13-27-501, MCA, is amended to read:
3 "13-27-501. Secretary of state to certify ballot form. (1) The secretary of state shall furnish to the
4 official of each county responsible for preparation of the ballots, at the same time as the election administrator
5 certifies the names of the persons who are candidates for offices to be filled at the election, a certified copy of
6 the form in which each statewide ballot issue to be voted on by the people at that election is to appear on the
7 ballot.
8 (2) The secretary of state shall list for each ballot issue:
9 (a) the number;
10 (b) the method of placement on the ballot;
11 (c) the title;
12 (d) the attorney general's explanatory statement, if applicable;
13 (e) the fiscal statement, if applicable;
14 (f) the statement of purpose and implication if not otherwise listed as the title pursuant to 13-27-
15 212;
16 (g) the yes and no statement; and
17 (h) a statement that the statewide ballot issue conflicts with one or more issues, referenced by
18 number, that also appear on the ballot, if applicable; and
19 (i) for a statewide initiative, the summary results of the legislative poll provided for in [section 1],
20 listed by the majority vote within each political party as follows:
21 [Most or Every] [partisan affiliation] legislator(s) voted to [support, oppose, or to not take a position on]
22 [statewide initiative number and title]; and
23 (j) for a statewide referendum, the summary results of the legislative referral vote, listed by the
24 majority vote within each political party as follows:
25 [Most or Every] [partisan affiliation] legislator(s) voted to [support, oppose, or to not take a position on]
26 [statewide referendum number and title].
27 (3) When required to do so, the secretary of state shall use for each ballot issue the title of the
28 legislative act or legislative constitutional proposal or the title provided by the attorney general or district court.
